# Divemap Project Standards

See core-essentials.mdc for universal Docker/env rules.

## Docker Container Management
- Use docker to manage containers
- Never start services directly on system
- Use `docker logs --since` for efficient log filtering

## Python Development
```bash
cd backend
source divemap_venv/bin/activate
export PYTHONPATH="/home/kargig/src/divemap/backend/divemap_venv/lib/python3.11/site-packages:$PYTHONPATH"
pip install package_name
```

## Node.js Development
```bash
docker exec divemap_frontend npm install package_name
docker exec divemap_frontend npm start
docker exec divemap_frontend npm run build
```

## Docker Commands
```bash
docker-compose up -d          # Start services
docker-compose down            # Stop services
docker exec divemap_frontend npm install package_name

# Restart specific service
docker restart divemap_frontend
```

## Docker Logging
```bash
docker logs divemap_frontend --since 5m | tail -20
docker logs divemap_backend --since 10m | grep -i "error\|warning"
```

## Credentials
Credentials in `local_testme` file. Use when necessary.

## Security
- Never install packages globally
- Never commit secrets to git
- Use .env files for local development
- Use pinned versions in requirements.txt
